All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Admin
Represents the administrator of the photo album application with the ability to manage users and regenerate the stock album with default photos.
AdminController
This class serves as the controller for the Admin view in a JavaFX application.
Album
Represents an album in the photo album application, holding a collection of photos and related details.
AlbumController
Controller for the album view in the photo album application.
LoginController
This class serves as the controller for the login view in a JavaFX application.
LogoutController
The LogoutController interface defines the default behavior for controllers that have the functionality to log out a user and save their data.
Navigatable
The Navigatable interface provides default methods for scene navigation and popup handling within a JavaFX application.
NonAdminController
This class is the controller for the non-admin user interface of the photo album application.
Persistence
Handles the persistence layer of the photo album application, managing the saving and loading of user and album data to and from the disk.
Photo
Represents a photograph in the photo album application, including its metadata such as tags and caption.
Photos
Main entry point for the Photos application.
SearchController
Controller for the search functionality within the photo album application.
Tag
A record for a tag associated with a photo, which includes a name and a value.
User
Represents a user in the photo album application with functionality to manage personal albums, search for photos by tags and date range, and maintain a viewable album.
